PPG-DaLiA dataset
=================

Citation:
  Reiss, A., Indlekofer, I., Schmidt, P. and Van Laerhoven, K. (2019).
  "Deep PPG: large-scale heart rate estimation with convolutional neural
  networks." Sensors, 19(14), 3079.
  DOI: 10.3390/s19143079

Source:
  UCI Machine Learning Repository — https://archive.ics.uci.edu/dataset/495/ppg+dalia

License:
  Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International (CC BY-NC 4.0).
  Academic / non-commercial use only.
  https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/

What's committed here:
  extracts/S1.npz, extracts/S6.npz — wrist BVP @ 64 Hz, ECG-derived HR labels
  @ 0.5 Hz, and activity codes @ 4 Hz for two representative subjects. Stripped
  from the full ~1.5 GB per-subject pickles (which include chest ECG @ 700 Hz,
  EMG, EDA, accelerometer, etc. — all unused by this project).

What's NOT committed:
  The full PPG-DaLiA pickles (S1..S15, ~21 GB total) and the source archive
  PPG_FieldStudy.zip (~1.2 GB). These are fetched on demand by
  scripts/fetch_dalia.py and stripped to per-subject extracts by
  scripts/make_dalia_extracts.py — both kept local-only via .gitignore.

Why two subjects:
  Mirrors the BIDMC cache pattern (bidmc01-03 committed; 04-53 on-demand).
  Two subjects are enough for CI smoke tests and the public README's demos.
  The full SQI-training workflow (Phase 3) requires all 15 subjects locally.
